{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17642040","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17642040"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:35:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:35:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17925"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17925","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17925"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.94,0,0.04,0.01,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10639"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76894"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10639","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10639"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17925"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62399"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24783"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24785"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76894","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76894"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 41-year-old female presents to her General Practitioner with blurred vision for the past year. She describes it as \u0022dark floating spots\u0022.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a microvascular complication of type 1 diabetes?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Retinopathy","Coronary artery disease","Peripheral artery disease","Hypertension","Stroke"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERetinopathy\u003C/strong\u003E is a microvascular complication of type 1 diabetes, resulting from damage to the small blood vessels in the retina. It is one of the most common causes of vision loss in people with diabetes and requires regular screening to detect early changes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoronary artery disease\u003C/strong\u003E is a macrovascular complication of diabetes, involving the large blood vessels supplying the heart.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPeripheral artery disease\u003C/strong\u003E is another macrovascular complication, affecting the large blood vessels in the limbs. It is associated with an increased risk of cardiovascular events.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypertension\u003C/strong\u003E is a common comorbidity in people with diabetes but is not a direct microvascular complication. It can exacerbate both microvascular and macrovascular complications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStroke\u003C/strong\u003E is a macrovascular complication, resulting from damage to the large blood vessels supplying the brain.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Microvascular complications of type 1 diabetes include retinopathy, nephropathy, and neuropathy.","Diabetic retinopathy is characterised by damage to the small blood vessels in the retina.","Diabetic nephropathy involves damage to the kidney\u0027s filtering units, leading to proteinuria."],"references":["DiMeglio LA, Evans-Molina C, Oram RA. Type 1 diabetes. Lancet. 2018 Jun 16;391(10138):2449-2462. doi: 10.1016/S0140-6736(18)31320-5. PMID: 29916386; PMCID: PMC6661119","Lucier J, Mathias PM. Type 1 Diabetes. 2024 Oct 5. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29939535","Giwa AM, Ahmed R, Omidian Z, Majety N, Karakus KE, Omer SM, Donner T, Hamad ARA. Current understandings of the pathogenesis of type 1 diabetes: Genetics to environment. World J Diabetes. 2020 Jan 15;11(1):13-25. doi: 10.4239/wjd.v11.i1.13. PMID: 31938470; PMCID: PMC6927819","Kahanovitz L, Sluss PM, Russell SJ. Type 1 Diabetes - A Clinical Perspective. Point Care. 2017 Mar;16(1):37-40. doi: 10.1097/POC.0000000000000125. PMID: 28943810; PMCID: PMC5606981"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62399"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17925"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62399","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62399"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-05T18:24:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T18:24:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10639"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76894"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4926","links":{"self":"https://app